Julian McGhee-Sumner\n| before_party = Conservative Party (UK)\n| after_election = \n| after_party = \n}}\nThe '''2019 Wokingham Borough Council election''' took place on Thursday 2 May 2019. That was the same day as other [[2019 United Kingdom local elections|United Kingdom local elections]] in order to elect members of [[Wokingham (borough)|Wokingham]] [[Unitary authority|Unitary]] Council in [[Berkshire]], England. One third of the council was up for election.\n\nBefore the election, the composition of the council was\n*[[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]] 41\n*[[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrat]] 8\n*[[Labour Party(UK)|Labour]] 3\n*[[Independent (politician)|Independent]] 2\n\n==Background==\nSince the last round of elections, there has been 1 by-election in Evendons in 2019, which was won by the Liberal Democrats. Richard Dolinski resigned from the Conservative Party to sit as an independent as a result of an internal vote of no confidence being put forward and subsequently passed against Cllr Charlotte Haitham-Taylor which led to her resignation as the Leader of the Council<ref>https://www.inyourarea.co.uk/news/wokingham-councillor-resigns-as-tories-turmoil-continues/</ref>\n\nThe composition of the council before the election was as follows:\n{| style=\"width:60%; text-align:center;\"\n|+ \u2193\n|- style=\"color:white;\"\n| style=\"background:{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}; width:75.9%;\" | '''41'''\n| style=\"background:{{Liberal Democrats (UK)/meta/color}}; width:14.8%;\" | '''8'''\n| style=\"background:{{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}; width:5.6%;\" | '''3'''\n| style=\"background:{{Independent (politician)/meta/color}}; width:3.7%;\" | '''2'''\n|-\n| <span style=\"color:{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}};\">{{abbr|'''CON'''|{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/shortname}}}}</span>\n| <span style=\"color:{{Liberal Democrats (UK)/meta/color}};\">{{abbr|'''LD'''|{{Liberal Democrats (UK)/meta/shortname}}}}</span>\n| <span style=\"color:{{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}};\">{{abbr|'''LAB'''|{{Labour Party (UK)/meta/shortname}}}}</span>\n| <span style=\"color:{{Independent (politician)/meta/color}};\">{{abbr|'''IND'''|{{Independent (politician)/meta/shortname}}}}</span>\n|}\n\nAfter the election, the composition of the council became:\n{| style=\"width:60%; text-align:center;\"\n|+ \u2193\n|- style=\"color:white;\"\n| style=\"background:{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}; width:57.4%;\" | '''31'''\n| style=\"background:{{Liberal Democrats (UK)/meta/color}}; width:29.6%;\" | '''16'''\n| style=\"background:{{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}; width:7.4%;\" | '''4'''\n| style=\"background:{{Independent (politician)/meta/color}}; width:5.5%;\" | '''3'''\n|-\n| <span style=\"color:{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}};\">{{abbr|'''CON'''|{{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/shortname}}}}</span>\n| <span style=\"color:{{Liberal Democrats (UK)/meta/color}};\">{{abbr|'''LD'''|{{Liberal Democrats (UK)/meta/shortname}}}}</span>\n| <span style=\"color:{{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}};\">{{abbr|'''LAB'''|{{Labour Party (UK)/meta/shortname}}}}</span>\n| <span style=\"color:{{Independent (politician)/meta/color}};\">{{abbr|'''IND'''|{{Independent (politician)/meta/shortname}}}}</span>\n|}\n\n==Election result==\n\n{{Election summary begin|title = Wokingham Local Election Result 2019}}\n\n{{Election summary party|\n  |party      = Conservative Party (UK)\n  |seats      = 31\n  |gain       = 0\n  |loss       = 10\n  |net        = {{decrease}}10\n  |seats %    = 57.4%\n  |votes %    = 37.3%\n  |votes      = 14,625\n  |plus/minus = {{decrease}}7.8%\n}}\n{{Election summary party|\n  |party      = Liberal Democrats (UK)\n  |seats      = 16\n  |gain       = 8\n  |loss       = 0\n  |net        = {{increase}}8\n  |seats %    = 29.6%\n  |votes %    = 39.4%\n  |votes      = 15,444\n  |plus/minus = {{increase}}7.7%\n}}\n{{Election summary party|\n  |party      = Labour Party (UK)\n  |seats      = 4\n  |gain       = 1\n  |loss       = 0